Generic real-time engine simulation environment for full thermodynamic simulation of various gas turbine engine configurations.
Developed for fight-simulation facilities, hence it must be efficiently solved on a real-time basis with sufficient speed.
Models the engine components using Component maps and thermodynamic equations.
Implemented in Matlab-Simulink, due to its modeling flexibility in the case of coupling differentiated components and subsystem (especially control system) models.
Military after-burning turbofans, as well as common turbo-shaft engines are simulated.

